# Demonstrates the gotchas and commands sections.
# Gotchas warn about sharp edges and known issues.
# Commands tell agents (and humans) how to build, test, and run the project.

version: 1

summary: |
  Legacy data migration service. Reads records from a MySQL 5.7
  database and writes them to PostgreSQL 15. Handles schema
  differences, data type conversions, and incremental sync.
  This service has several known issues documented as gotchas below.

gotchas:
  # Each gotcha has text (the warning) and optional tags for retrieval.
  # Gotchas are the "do not touch the hot stove" section of .ctx.

  - text: |
      CRITICAL: The MySQL connection pool leaks connections when a
      migration batch fails mid-stream. If you see "Too many connections"
      errors, restart the service and check src/mysql-pool.ts:67 for
      the missing connection.release() in the error path.
    tags: [mysql, connection-pool, bugs, critical]
    verified_at: "a1b2c3d"
    locked: true

  - text: |
      The date conversion logic in src/converters/dates.ts silently
      drops timezone information for dates before 1970. This is a known
      MySQL limitation with TIMESTAMP columns. Use DATETIME columns
      for pre-1970 dates, and see the workaround in dates.ts:112.
    tags: [dates, mysql, data-conversion]
    verified_at: "b2c3d4e"
    locked: false

  - text: |
      The incremental sync relies on a "last_synced_at" cursor stored
      in the migrations table. If you truncate that table, the next
      run will attempt a FULL re-sync which can take 12+ hours on
      production data. Always use the --reset-cursor flag instead
      of direct table manipulation.
    tags: [sync, migration, operations]
    verified_at: "c3d4e5f"
    locked: false

  - text: |
      The PostgreSQL COPY command used in bulk inserts does not support
      upserts. If a record already exists, the batch will fail with a
      unique constraint violation. Use the --upsert-mode flag to switch
      to individual INSERT ON CONFLICT statements (slower but safe).
    tags: [postgresql, bulk-insert, operations]
    verified_at: "d4e5f6a"
    locked: false

  - text: |
      Environment variable DB_MYSQL_SSL must be set to "true" in
      production. The default is "false" for local development. If
      you see "Access denied" errors in staging/production, check
      this variable first.
    tags: [config, environment, ssl]
    verified_at: "e5f6a7b"
    locked: false

commands:
  # Build commands
  build: "npm run build"
  build:watch: "npm run build -- --watch"

  # Test commands with explanations
  test: "npm test"
  test:integration: "npm run test:integration -- --timeout 60000"
  test:mysql: "docker compose up -d mysql && npm run test:mysql"

  # Run commands
  dev: "npm run dev -- --dry-run"
  migrate: "npm run migrate -- --batch-size 1000"
  migrate:full: "npm run migrate -- --full --batch-size 5000"
  migrate:resume: "npm run migrate -- --resume"

  # Utility commands
  lint: "npm run lint"
  typecheck: "npx tsc --noEmit"
  validate:schema: "npm run validate:schema"

  # Operations commands
  status: "npm run status"
  reset-cursor: "npm run reset-cursor -- --confirm"

tags: [migration, mysql, postgresql, data-pipeline]
